@startuml
title From Rust Value to Memory Location

start
:Student writes Rust value;
:Compiler assigns type and layout rules;
:Program uses variable name or reference;
:Runtime uses virtual memory address;
:OS and CPU map to physical memory;
:Hardware reads or writes bytes;
stop

note right
  The variable name is not the cell.
  The reference is not the molecule.
  Each layer is a representation.
end note

@enduml

